SIMPLE: lichee
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: lichee
<hw>lichee</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A Chinese tree
(<spn>Litchi chinensis</spn>) cultivated especially in the Philippines
and India for its edible fruit, the <prod>litchi nut</prod>; sometimes
placed in the genus <gen>Nephelium</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> litchi, litchi tree, <spn>Litchi chinensis</spn>,
Nephelium litchi.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A Chinese fruit having a thin brittle shell
enclosing a sweet jellylike pulp and a single seed; often
dried.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> litchi, litchi nut, litchee, lichi, leechee,
lychee.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lichen</ent>⟦br⟧
